A Lament for Hip-Hop in Somalia *

In 1991, Somalia, traditionally a fertile horned country that was famous for it’s cattle wealth and agriculture, was split into three different parts by land warriors from neighboring countries, these three different parts are also the cause of one of the worst Africa’s refugee crisis of recent times. South-West and Central parts of Somalia was controlled by the U.S allied republican Somali government, the North-East was occupied by the one and only successful TNG, and the North part of Somalia was under total occupation by Syrian backed Adal Sultanate. col. Yusuf Kenadid.

The American allied Somali professional suspect ex-exil Somali government managed to buy 10 to 15 kilos of cocaine per day from a Mexican Dr., in the 1990’s, whose name is yet to be revealed by historians. the American Somalis mostly used this powder to share around to their colleagues and friends, until one day an unknown female student of USM declared school wide that the powder in question was poor grade of cocaine and not our traditional khat which is also the national flower of Somalia.
